<p>Children&rsquo;s Ballet is divided into 3 areas of study; Pre-School Ballet, Ballet I, and Ballet II. Each area has, at its core, a codified syllabus designed to facilitate the maximum physical, mental and emotional development appropriate to the age and physical ability of each student. We provide a happy and child-friendly environment where each child&rsquo;s dreams and expressions are nurtured and valued.</p><p><strong>Summer Camps</strong><br><em>Angelina Ballerina</em><span> (June 12, 13 &amp; 14)</span><br><span>Join Angelina and her friends! Learn to express yourself through creative movement and ballet basics! Enjoy learning positions, partnering and props. Every day, we will sing, dance, color and create a special craft to use as your twirl, hop, prance and glide. The Angelina Ballerina camp is designed for ages 3-8 with or without dance training. Wear your favorite leotard, princess gown or costume. Space is limited. Camp is from 10:30am- 12:30pm.</span></p><p><em>Cinderella Ballerina </em><span>(June 19, 20 &amp; 21)</span><br><span>Based around the fairy tale ballet, the curriculum includes a daily ballet class, ballet mime, costume showing, music, games, arts and crafts (each student will make princess tiaras and a scrapbook which they can take home), and m</span></p><h4><em><span id="internal-source-marker_0.8816895448533697">Jazz and Hip Hop </span></em><span>(June 26, 27 &amp; 28)</span><br><span>Get ready to move! This high energy camp is the perfect way to have fun this summer. Come out and learn fun moves and a funky dance routine. We will be rocking out to One Direction, Justin Bieber, and Beyonce. Please wear comfortable clothing to move in and sneakers or jazz shoes. This camp is for boys and girls ages 8-12. </span><br><br><em><span>Princess Day Camp</span></em><span>(July 19)</span><br><span>Does your little one love to dress up? All 3-8 year old girls are royally invited to The Princess Camp hosted by real Ballerina Victoria Simo. Your little princess will receive an introduction to ballet technique while learning about fun fairytale characters and famous ballet stories. This day includes a magical tea party and princess wands and tiaras to dance with. The tiny Cinderellas and Snow Whites will also have dress-up time and craft time. Dancers may wear their favorite tutu, princess gown or costume. No previous dance experience needed. The day camp is from 12:30-2:30pm at the Northwest center.</span></h4><p><span>﻿</span></p><p>&nbsp;Fall Enrollment</p><p><strong>Pre-School Ballet</strong></p><p>Pre-School Ballet provides fun, creatively themed classes that are designed to appeal to each child&rsquo;s imagination, introducing fundamental movements and ballet vocabulary. Children are inspired to move artistically through imagery, role play and exposure to a diverse selection of music. Glittering wands, ribbons, hoops, and an array of colorful props are all used to stimulate young imaginations and encourage self-expression.Through dance, children are provided with opportunities for achievement and enjoyment while developing muscle control, coordination, creativity, spatial awareness, social skills and confidence.</p><p><span id="internal-source-marker_0.8816895448533697">Ballet I</span><br><span>The one hour Ballet I class is for children ages 6-8. Starting in Ballet I, students begin formal training in traditional classical ballet. The syllabus progresses at a rate that allows the student to learn the exercises correctly and with full physicality. Repetition and slow careful work is emphasized, with the students learning discipline and control of their bodies. By introducing students to the basic steps, positions, postures and traditions of classical ballet, the Ballet I curriculum enhances both cognitive and physical development at this important time.</span><br><br><span>Ballet II</span><br><span>In Ballet II, young dancers&nbsp; ages 9-12 add new dance skills and larger movements. They begin work on refining their form and technique towards the achievement of precision. Students begin more advanced technique work in their barre exercises and combinations. Vocabulary and classical dance movement will be taught. Dancers will explore balance, many kinds of jumps and combining several dance movements together. Students develop skills associated with academic success including self-discipline, self-confidence and the ability to concentrate and collaborate.</span><br><br><span>Jazz and Hip Hop</span><br><span>This hour long class combines fun, easy-to-follow dance moves to popular music for boys and girls ages 6-12. The non-competitive atmosphere is the perfect setting to introduce your child to jazz and hip hop dance. </span></p><p><strong>﻿</strong>At the end of the year, students participate in the Spring Gala during regular class time at the studios.</p><p>Enrolling now! Classes begin August 2, 2012.</p>
